 Ikorodu  Contrary to the video making the rounds of an attack on Ikorodu police station, Igbogbo, Lagos by hoodlums, the state police command has refuted the claims, stating that there was no attack on any of its facilities.  “In the bid to rescue the other male suspect, the agitated crowd also attacked the policemen.  The suspect was subsequently rescued and taken to hospital for treatment,” he said.
 
Also, the Lagos state commissioner of police, Hakeem Odumosu, has condemned jungle justice and called for a discreet investigation into the case.
 
He promised to tackle such inhumane acts. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .